all the way from nine to...

04:32.870 --> 04:34.500
36 on the first zoom, so...

04:34.700 --> 04:36.690
Oh. I made breakfast.

04:39.530 --> 04:42.350
We didn't really know
what to expect.

04:42.540 --> 04:44.350
[Warren] Again
with the legs, man.

04:44.550 --> 04:46.390
[Eddie] Dude, I know.

04:46.590 --> 04:48.230
- [Warren] I'm a leg guy,
you know?
- Hey, Daisy.

04:48.430 --> 04:49.980
- [Warren] That's just a fact.
- Hi.

04:50.180 --> 04:52.310
- And those legs?
- Mm-hmm. I mean...

04:52.510 --> 04:54.860
They just got me
a little distracted

04:55.060 --> 04:56.820
- is all I'm saying.
- Warren, right?

04:57.020 --> 04:58.570
Yeah.

04:58.770 --> 05:00.880
You know it's not my job
not to turn you on, right?

05:02.800 --> 05:05.280
I-I do... now.

05:05.480 --> 05:07.540
Great.

05:07.740 --> 05:09.830
- [chuckles]
- [Billy] All right, everybody.

05:10.030 --> 05:11.920
I just want to say a few things

05:12.120 --> 05:13.710
before we get started.
First off,

05:13.910 --> 05:15.920
we have a new member
of the band.

05:16.120 --> 05:18.550
So let's hear it
for Daisy Jones.

05:18.750 --> 05:20.760
[cheering, whooping]

05:20.960 --> 05:23.260
- [Warren] Welcome.
- Thank you for being here

05:23.460 --> 05:25.300
and for doing this with us.

05:25.500 --> 05:26.720
Thank you for having me.

05:26.920 --> 05:28.770
So, it's been what, four weeks?

05:28.970 --> 05:30.890
I wrote a song.
[clears throat] Well, actually,

05:31.090 --> 05:33.600
I've written about 20 songs
I'd like to play for you guys.

05:33.800 --> 05:35.560
Sorry. I wasn't trying
to cut you off or anything.

05:35.760 --> 05:37.940
I was just...
I'm excited about it, so...

05:38.140 --> 05:40.840
[Billy] Okay.

05:44.090 --> 05:45.410
What?

05:45.610 --> 05:49.200
The songs were all written
and ready to go.

05:49.400 --> 05:52.080
Well, Daisy,
the great news is, we, uh...

05:52.280 --> 05:54.380
we actually have,

05:54.570 --> 05:56.840
what, 13 songs
for the album, so...

05:57.040 --> 05:59.630
Yeah, I mean,
why don't we play you some,

05:59.830 --> 06:01.380
and then, uh, you can have
a listen, see if you...

06:01.580 --> 06:03.380
feel strongly
about any of them or,

06:03.580 --> 06:05.430
you know, want to add anything.
You know?

06:05.630 --> 06:06.890
I mean, can you imagine?

06:07.090 --> 06:09.310
I could not have been nicer.

06:09.510 --> 06:10.730
We could play the, uh...

06:10.920 --> 06:12.350
- the new one for Daisy.
- Mm.

06:12.550 --> 06:14.240
Yeah.

06:15.290 --> 06:17.270
Yeah, I think
you're gonna dig this one.

06:17.470 --> 06:21.090
Let me guess, it's about
your wife and the rain.

06:23.050 --> 06:25.870
[laughs] Oh, my God.

06:26.060 --> 06:28.910
[laughs] I think it was called
"She's the Storm."

06:29.110 --> 06:30.410
Seriously.

06:30.610 --> 06:33.120
[laughs]

06:33.320 --> 06:35.540
- [chuckles] That funny?
- No.

06:35.740 --> 06:37.290
Sorry, did you want
to say something?

06:37.490 --> 06:39.420
No, I'm just...
I mean, I'm not here

06:39.620 --> 06:42.210
to sing harmony on a bunch
of love songs about your wife.

06:42.410 --> 06:44.090
Right?

06:44.290 --> 06:45.930
You know, I mean,

06:46.130 --> 06:48.430
if we're gonna... if we're
in a band, then the album has

06:48.630 --> 06:50.470
to be just as much mine
as it is yours.

06:50.670 --> 06:53.100
As it is Karen's
and Graham's and Warren's

06:53.300 --> 06:54.690
and that guy's.

06:54.890 --> 06:57.310
You know?

06:57.510 --> 06:59.610
She was saying things
I'd been saying since '69.

06:59.810 --> 07:02.820
I mean, shouldn't we at least
talk about a direction?

07:03.020 --> 07:04.820
Is there a concept, a big idea

07:05.020 --> 07:06.490
you have for the record, or...?

07:06.690 --> 07:08.530
[Karen] Actually, I-I agree.

07:08.730 --> 07:11.540
What? I-I think
it's a good conversation.

07:11.740 --> 07:13.290
- [Eddie] You know what I think?
- Oh, God.

07:13.490 --> 07:15.460
I think this should be
a rock and roll record.

07:15.660 --> 07:16.710
[sighs] Thank you, Eddie.

07:16.910 --> 07:18.250
Thank you so much
for your input.

07:18.450 --> 07:20.170
- [Eddie] No, I'm serious.
- [Daisy chuckles]

07:20.370 --> 07:22.050
Of course it's gonna be
a rock and roll record, man.

07:22.250 --> 07:23.340
What the fuck?

07:23.540 --> 07:25.010
I mean, is it, though?

07:25.210 --> 07:27.130
'Cause, I mean, like,
a lot of these songs are

07:27.330 --> 07:29.640
sounding like, like,
well, well, pop songs, man.

07:29.840 --> 07:30.930
[mouthing]

07:31.130 --> 07:32.140
Like Sonny and Cher shit.

07:32.340 --> 07:34.350
You know, are we
a pop band now, or...?

07:34.550 --> 07:36.980
All right?
I mean, rock and roll should be

07:37.180 --> 07:39.230
passion, pain, anger.

07:39.430 --> 07:41.320
- Mm.
- Sleeping with some girl
you don't know,

07:41.510 --> 07:43.710
not making sweet love
to your wife, for Chrissakes.

07:45.250 --> 07:46.740
No offense, Billy.

07:46.940 --> 07:48.910
Sort of what
I was trying to say.

07:49.110 --> 07:51.370
- How about
some African drums?
- Great idea.

07:51.570 --> 07:53.200
We could do a song just
vocals and piano.

07:53.400 --> 07:55.160
Yeah, I-I'd like to write some
of my own bass parts for once.

07:55.360 --> 07:56.330
- You know, why not?
- [Daisy] Great!

07:56.530 --> 07:57.750
I knew this was
a fucking terrible idea.

07:57.950 --> 07:58.960
What's the bad idea?

07:59.160 --> 08:00.880
Wait, I mean,
you invited me here.

08:01.080 --> 08:02.710
Yeah, well, maybe
that was a mistake, Daisy.

08:02.910 --> 08:04.770
- All right?
- Are you done?

08:06.060 --> 08:08.300
Are you? Jesus Christ.

08:08.500 --> 08:10.680
You're acting like a bunch
of kindergarteners.

08:10.880 --> 08:13.060
Just maybe the two of you
can go someplace

08:13.260 --> 08:15.560
and work on something together,
how about that?

08:15.760 --> 08:17.600
Either way,
the door is right there,

08:17.800 --> 08:19.650
so go on
and get the fuck out of here,

08:19.840 --> 08:22.110
'cause I got shit to do.

08:22.310 --> 08:24.460
Go, goddamn it!

08:26.790 --> 08:28.360
Come on.

08:28.560 --> 08:30.240
[Billy sighs]

08:30.440 --> 08:33.010
[door opens, closes]

08:34.220 --> 08:36.080
Hey, yeah, so what about us?

08:36.280 --> 08:37.540
I could care less.

08:37.740 --> 08:39.670
So where should we go?

08:39.860 --> 08:41.960
- Apple Pan.
- What?

08:42.160 --> 08:43.250
I'm hungry.

08:43.450 --> 08:44.750
It's, like,
10:00 in the morning.

08:44.950 --> 08:47.150
Well, I can't work
if I'm hungry.

08:51.240 --> 08:53.550
[♪ Barry Manilow:
"Could It Be Magic"]

08:53.750 --> 08:56.390
♪ <i>Could this be the magic</i> ♪

08:56.590 --> 08:58.430
♪ <i>At last?</i> ♪

08:58.630 --> 09:00.240
[shuts radio off]

09:01.660 --> 09:05.320
♪ <i>Oh, let me know</i> ♪

09:05.520 --> 09:07.940
[music stops]

09:08.140 --> 09:10.490
♪ <i>And, baby, I want you</i> ♪

09:10.690 --> 09:12.320
- Turn it off.
- It's a good song.

09:12.520 --> 09:15.370
- It's my fucking car.
- Oh, my lord.

09:15.570 --> 09:16.990
- [bell dings]
- Hey, there.

09:17.190 --> 09:18.200
What'll it be?

09:18.400 --> 09:19.620
Two hickory burgers,
medium rare.

09:19.820 --> 09:21.500
And two sides of fries, please.

09:21.700 --> 09:23.420
I don't need you
to order for me.

09:23.620 --> 09:25.520
Well, good, 'cause I didn't.

09:30.110 --> 09:32.640
Yeah. I'll, uh,
I'll have the same.

09:32.830 --> 09:34.470
Coming right up.

09:34.670 --> 09:36.740
[music playing faintly]

09:40.660 --> 09:42.230
[sighs] All right, look.

09:42.430 --> 09:45.860
No good's gonna come out of us
fighting all the time.

09:46.060 --> 09:48.190
Well, how-how do you know that?

09:48.390 --> 09:50.490
- What?
- What do you know
about fighting?

09:50.690 --> 09:52.420
Nobody ever stands up to you.

09:56.010 --> 09:57.740
Can I ask you a question?

09:57.940 --> 09:59.120
Be my guest.

09:59.320 --> 10:00.830
Why are you so obsessed
with your wife?

10:01.030 --> 10:02.960
- [laughs] What?
- I met Camila. She's great,

10:03.160 --> 10:05.080
but why can't you write a song
about anything else?

10:05.280 --> 10:07.170
Is it...
are you afraid she's gonna...

10:07.370 --> 10:08.960
leave you or do you feel like
you're not good enough for her?

10:09.160 --> 10:10.710
What's the thing that...?

10:10.910 --> 10:12.170
- [chuckles] Daisy.
- Did you do something wrong?

10:12.370 --> 10:13.930
Daisy.

10:14.130 --> 10:16.010
I don't want to talk
to you about this, okay?

10:16.210 --> 10:17.740
- Okay.
- Okay.

10:20.120 --> 10:22.770
Okay. Two hickory burgers each.

10:22.970 --> 10:24.910
["Stumbled on Sublime"
plays on radio]

10:27.750 --> 10:31.940
♪ <i>I, I found you...</i>

10:32.140 --> 10:33.490
- Enjoy.
- Thank you.

10:33.690 --> 10:36.450
[music continues faintly]

10:36.650 --> 10:40.370
♪ <i>Stumbled on sublime</i> ♪

10:40.570 --> 10:43.080
♪ <i>I stumbled on sublime</i> ♪

10:43.280 --> 10:45.330
[humming chorus melody]

10:45.530 --> 10:49.920
♪ <i>Getting through the day</i>
<i>was always such a chore...</i>

10:50.120 --> 10:52.550
Do you like this song?

10:52.750 --> 10:54.470
- "Stumbled on Sublime"?
- Mm-hmm.

10:54.670 --> 10:56.430
- I mean,
everyone likes this song.
- I wrote it.

10:56.630 --> 10:58.260
What do you mean you "wrote it"?

10:58.460 --> 10:59.600
I mean I-I wrote it.

10:59.800 --> 11:01.060
Like you wrote "Honeycomb"?

11:01.260 --> 11:02.310
Kind of.

11:02.510 --> 11:03.350
[chuckles] Okay.

11:03.550 --> 11:04.940
I wrote the lyrics.

11:05.140 --> 11:07.020
Some of the melody.
Well, most of the melody.

11:07.220 --> 11:09.150
♪ <i>Stumbled on sublime...</i>

11:09.350 --> 11:10.610
Listen to the song.

11:10.810 --> 11:12.360
You think Wyatt Stone
could write this?

11:12.560 --> 11:15.570
♪ <i>She's all around your head</i> ♪

11:15.770 --> 11:19.700
♪ <i>She's dancing</i>
<i>on the edges of your mind...</i>

11:19.900 --> 11:22.840
[lyrics continue indistinctly]

11:29.140 --> 11:31.960
It's a, it's a great
fucking song, Daisy.

11:32.160 --> 11:34.050
Well, cool, man.

11:34.250 --> 11:35.760
Now that you dig it,

11:35.960 --> 11:38.030
maybe you can stop being
such a dick all the time.

11:39.070 --> 11:40.680
[laughs softly]

11:40.880 --> 11:42.640
[Warren] Hey, man, are you sure
you don't want to come?

11:42.840 --> 11:45.020
Well, I've already seen it.

11:45.220 --> 11:46.480
Yeah.

11:46.680 --> 11:48.060
You've seen it once.

11:48.260 --> 11:49.610
That's probably
the appropriate number of times

11:49.800 --> 11:51.020
to watch <i>Rollerball.</i>

11:51.220 --> 11:52.730
Not if you appreciate art,
brother.

11:52.930 --> 11:53.820
[laughs]

11:54.020 --> 11:55.360
It's a true
cinematic masterpiece.

11:55.560 --> 11:57.700
All right, well,
enjoy round two, gentlemen.

11:57.900 --> 11:59.370
Oh, I will.

11:59.560 --> 12:01.030
[laughs]

12:01.230 --> 12:03.080
[grunts softly]

12:03.280 --> 12:04.750
What are you guys up to?

12:04.940 --> 12:07.000
- Movies.
- Oh. <i>Rollerball</i> again?

12:07.200 --> 12:09.080
It's a fucking masterpiece.

12:09.280 --> 12:11.790
- Hey!
- [laughs]

12:11.990 --> 12:13.940
[music playing faintly]

12:16.980 --> 12:18.970
Hey, I was thinking, um,

12:19.170 --> 12:21.570
I'll come to the beach
with you today.

12:25.620 --> 12:27.600
I mean, why not?

12:27.800 --> 12:29.870
I got nothing else to do.

12:33.460 --> 12:35.460
Okay.

12:37.920 --> 12:39.920
Graham.

12:45.510 --> 12:46.930
Are we good?

12:48.350 --> 12:50.350
Of course we are.

12:52.140 --> 12:53.840
We're great.

12:54.040 --> 12:55.250
All right?

12:55.450 --> 12:58.260
Okay.

12:58.460 --> 13:01.780
- I'll go get my stuff then.
- [Graham] Yeah.

13:07.870 --> 13:09.390
[car horn honks]

13:09.590 --> 13:11.060
- Hey.
- [chuckles] How's it going?

13:11.260 --> 13:12.480
Oh, it's good.

13:12.680 --> 13:13.730
- You got it? Okay.
- How are you?

13:13.930 --> 13:15.710
- [Graham] Yeah.
- [car door opens]

13:18.380 --> 13:20.110
Hey, you coming?

13:20.310 --> 13:21.950
Why don't you guys
just go ahead?

13:22.150 --> 13:23.780
- Why, you all right?
- Yeah. [stammers]

13:23.980 --> 13:25.280
I just didn't realize
that it was...

13:25.480 --> 13:26.490
[Caroline] Oh, no, no, no!

13:26.690 --> 13:28.120
It's totally fine. Yeah, hop in.

13:28.320 --> 13:29.710
- See?
- [chuckles]

13:29.900 --> 13:31.830
Don't be weird.

13:32.030 --> 13:33.210
Let's go.

13:33.410 --> 13:35.810
- [engine starts]
- Cool.

13:39.770 --> 13:41.090
Wow.

13:41.290 --> 13:42.630
Whose house is this?

13:42.830 --> 13:45.070
You've never been here before?

13:46.990 --> 13:49.640
- I can't say I have.
- [sighs] Okay.

13:49.840 --> 13:51.310
- Where is...
- Uh, Daisy?

13:51.510 --> 13:53.400
What? That key...

13:53.600 --> 13:54.770
[scoffs]

13:54.970 --> 13:56.270
What are you doing?

13:56.470 --> 13:58.120
I'm looking for a key, Billy.

14:01.040 --> 14:02.490
I mean, Jesus...

14:02.690 --> 14:03.740
Daisy.

14:03.940 --> 14:05.720
Ha!

14:06.720 --> 14:08.620
